    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Ask
    An Ask kind of order.
    AskComparator
    Ask orders are to be sorted from lower to higher.
    Bid
    A Bid kind of order
    BidComparator
    Bit orders are to be sorted from higher (more interesting) to lower (less interesting).
    HalfBook<T>
    A bid or ask book (depending on parameters).
    IOrder
    Standard members of an Order object
    ITrade
    Sets the required fields of an object that records the details of a trade.
    Order
    A general Order object.
    Orderbook
    An Orderbook contains two HalfBook objects, one for Ask objects and one for Bid objects.
    OrderOutcome
    Captures the outcome of an order processing operation HalfBook.processOrder(IOrder, int) An arraylist of Trade objects keeps the resulting trades while a IOrder implementing object captures the unfulfilled order (which my have zero quantity, i.e., the order was fully fulfilled).
    Security
    A security to be traded in the exchange (e.g., stock, option, or bond).
    SecurityList
    A simple list of securities.
    Trade
    An object that record a trade even and its details.
    Trader
    Represents agents that trade in, e.g., an exchange.
    TraderInstitutional
    An institutional Trader, like a bank or pension fund.
    TraderRetail
    A retail trader like ordinary folk who like to invest.
